{"TopicId":213431,"ForumId":196,"TopicTitle":"Ship spins uncontrollably in LKO","CreatedByName":"PupLord","CreatedById":226716,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T22:07:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"PupLord","CreatedById":226716,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T22:07:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis happens with every ship I leave in orbit at 1x timewarp, it just spins (and accelerates the spinning) forever. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E do nothing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lorunification","CreatedById":135645,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T22:52:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you use probe cores instead of manned pods? It may be that you lose control due to no connection to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E. You can check if the antenna in the navball bottom right is green or orange. Adding an antenna to she ship helps. Not sure if this is a bug or a feature for now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ShmackedSloth","CreatedById":226722,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T22:55:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe inputs for roll and yaw are crossed with the roll and yaw outputs with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E controls.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"skogs","CreatedById":226458,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T23:44:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis has nothing to do with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 The Krakken has visited a few of my craft and made them spin.\u00A0 I have partially recovered by pulsing the time warp to stop the spin...and so far every single time I end up with odd gaps in my craft.\u00A0 Small comm sat with fuel, engine, and probe control ... big gap in the middle as big as the fuel tank, but still functioning as a single unit.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Youre_Arent","CreatedById":226737,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T00:18:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this bug but not in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E, instead in low Mun orbit during landing. Haven\u2019t been to any other celestial bodies yet so I\u2019m not sure it just happens everywhere or not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xanatos","CreatedById":32071,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-01T20:41:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGot something similar which I reported just a second ago via the support page.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/d0BHwnPfzf0?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022Kerbal Space Program 2 Craft spins out of control\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I did find interessting is that the navball seems to be locked in this situation \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-01T20:41:47Z\u0022 title=\u002203/01/2023 08:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 1, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Xanatos\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdded additional thoughts\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"gussi111","CreatedById":212979,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-01T21:38:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/cCK8oPqWNfM?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022KSP 2: Sending a Rover to EVE...Despite the Kraken Attacks!\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt happened here\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}